# No country / currency selector in header

The merchant **permanently removed** the Shopify Markets country/region/currency dropdown from the lurafi theme header.

## Required behavior

- Header and mobile nav show a **language-only** selector (`locale_code` → POST `/localization`).
- Keep language labels visible; flags are decorative extras only (do not rely on flags alone).

## Never add or restore

- `country_code` form fields or `data-country-select`
- `HeaderCountrySelector`, `language-selector__select--country`
- `lurafi_published_country_csv`, `lurafi_country_order_csv` in Liquid
- Country/currency pills next to the language control in `sections/header.liquid`

## Allowed elsewhere

- `localization.country` / `cart.currency` for analytics, pricing JSON, and address forms (`sections/main-addresses.liquid`) — not a storefront country switcher.

## Build & QA guards

- `scripts/build-locales.mjs` must **not** inject country CSV into `snippets/language-selector.liquid` (build fails if country markers appear).
- `scripts/qa-commerce-debug.mjs` must fail when `[data-country-select]` is present on the storefront.

## If asked to add country selector

Decline and explain the language-only policy unless the user explicitly reverses this permanent removal.
